            ' Now it's time to buid the application as a Habitat artifact (<strong>.hart</strong>).
          p
            ' Building your application as a <strong>.hart</strong> package enables you to do things such as
          ul
            li export your application into a vareity of cloud-native formats,
            li get automated rebuilds when dependencies are updated,
            li and manage running services via the Habitat Supervisor, to name a few.
          p
            ' First, let's step into a <strong>Habitat Studio</strong> from the root of the <em>sample-node-app</em> repo, so that we have a clean room from which to biuld our artifacts.
          = code(:shell) do
            | $ hab studio enter
          p
